# 🩺 MedNotes AI — Setup Guide

## What is this project?

**MedNotes AI** is an AI-powered medical assistant that streamlines the patient-doctor journey. It has three phases:

1. **Pre-Consultation** — AI chatbot helps patients describe symptoms and book appointments with the right specialist
2. **Consultation** — Records and transcribes the doctor-patient conversation, then generates clinical notes using AI
3. **Post-Consultation** — RAG-powered chatbot lets both doctors and patients ask questions about past consultations

### Tech Stack
| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Frontend + Backend | **Next.js 16** (React 19, TypeScript) |
| Auth & Database | **Supabase** (PostgreSQL, RLS, Storage) |
| UI Components | **shadcn/ui** + Tailwind CSS v4 |
| AI Models | Gemini 2.5 Flash, Groq Llama 3.3, AssemblyAI, Amazon Nova 2 via OpenRouter |
| AI Orchestration | **Kestra** (Docker) |
| Deployment | Vercel |

---

## Step-by-Step Setup

### Step 1 — Install Node.js Dependencies

```bash
cd c:\Users\HP\OneDrive\Desktop\mednotes-ai\app
npm install
```

### Step 2 — Create a Supabase Project

1. Go to [https://supabase.com](https://supabase.com) and create a **free** account
2. Click **"New Project"** → give it a name like `mednotes-ai`
3. Set a database password (save it somewhere)
4. Wait for the project to provision

Once ready, go to **Project Settings → API** and copy:
- **Project URL** (looks like `https://xxxxx.supabase.co`)
- **Anon/Public Key** (the `anon` key)

### Step 3 — Set Up the Database

In your Supabase dashboard:

1. Go to **SQL Editor**
2. Run each migration file **in order** from `supabase/migrations/`:

| Order | File | What it creates |
|-------|------|-----------------|
| 1 | `001_create_profiles_table.sql` | `profiles` table with RLS + auto-create on signup |
| 2 | `002_create_core_tables.sql` | `appointments`, `consultations`, `documents`, `chat_messages` tables |
| 3 | `003_create_booking_chat_table.sql` | Booking chat history table |
| 4 | `004_create_test_doctor.sql` | Seed data for a test doctor |
| 5 | `005_allow_viewing_doctors.sql` | RLS policy for viewing doctor profiles |
| 6 | `006_create_doctor_availability.sql` | Doctor availability/schedule table |
| 7 | `007_add_chat_id_to_booking_chat.sql` | Adds chat_id column |
| 8 | `008_add_role_to_booking_chat.sql` | Adds role column |
| 9 | `009_add_booking_chat_id_to_appointments.sql` | Links booking chats to appointments |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Run them **in order** (001 → 009). Each builds on the previous one.

### Step 4 — Get API Keys

You need API keys from these services (all have **free tiers**):

| Service | Purpose | Get it at |
|---------|---------|-----------|
| **Gemini** | Main AI model (chat, booking) | [aistudio.google.com](https://aistudio.google.com/apikey) |
| **Groq** | Fallback AI model | [console.groq.com](https://console.groq.com/keys) |
| **AssemblyAI** | Audio transcription | [assemblyai.com](https://www.assemblyai.com/dashboard/signup) |
| **OpenRouter** | Consultation summaries (Amazon Nova 2) | [openrouter.ai](https://openrouter.ai/keys) |

### Step 5 — Create `.env.local`

Create a file called `.env.local` in the `app/` directory:

**File:** `c:\Users\HP\OneDrive\Desktop\mednotes-ai\app\.env.local`

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL="your-supabase-project-url"
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY="your-supabase-anon-key"
GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY="your-gemini-api-key"
GROQ_API_KEY="your-groq-api-key"
ASSEMBLYAI_API_KEY="your-assemblyai-api-key"
OPENROUTER_API_KEY="your-openrouter-api-key"
```

Replace each placeholder with your actual keys from Steps 2 and 4.

### Step 6 — Run the App

```bash
cd c:\Users\HP\OneDrive\Desktop\mednotes-ai\app
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) in your browser.

### Step 7 (Optional) — Set Up Kestra Agent Workflows

This is only needed for the **consultation recording → transcription → AI summary** pipeline. The basic app (booking, chat) works without it.

1. Install [Docker Desktop](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/)
2. Start Kestra:
   ```bash
   cd c:\Users\HP\OneDrive\Desktop\mednotes-ai\agent
   docker-compose up -d
   ```
3. Open Kestra UI at [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080)
4. Import the two workflow files from `agent/workflow/`:
   - `audio_transcription.yml`
   - `ai_summary_workflow.yml`

