## Demo Credentials

Once the database is seeded (after running migration `004`), you can log in with:

| Role | Email | Password |
|------|-------|----------|
| Patient | `hari@user.com` | `testpass` |
| Doctor | `test@doctor.com` | `testpass` |

> [!NOTE]
> These test users are created by migration `004_create_test_doctor.sql`. You may also need to create these users in **Supabase Auth** (Authentication → Users → Add User) with the same email/password for login to work.

---

## What You Can Do Without All API Keys

| Feature | Required Keys |
|---------|--------------|
| Login, Dashboard UI | Supabase only |
| AI Booking Chat | Supabase + Gemini (or Groq as fallback) |
| Post-consultation RAG Chat | Supabase + Gemini (or Groq) |
| Audio Transcription | Supabase + AssemblyAI + Kestra |
| AI Summary/Report | Supabase + OpenRouter + Kestra |

You can start with just **Supabase + Gemini** to explore most features.
